.. NOTE:
{rbrr_gcb_machine_type}
is a Compute Engine machine type (e.g., `e2-standard-2`), consumed at pool creation time.
Pool scales to zero workers when idle — no idle cost accrues.
.. NOTE: The two variants differ only in egress posture. The `airgap` body declares `networkConfig.egressOption: NO_PUBLIC_EGRESS`, which Cloud Build enforces at pool level — builds routed through the airgap pool cannot reach the public internet regardless of build configuration. Awaiting the LRO terminal state at create time surfaces machine-type quota denial here rather than as a downstream "workerpool not found" at the {rbtoe_per_pool_probe_submit} step.
